                            <comment id="13124636" author="brandon.williams" created="Tue, 11 Oct 2011 01:05:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ISTM the easiest thing to do here is actually use 2 when a user specifies 1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13127248" author="jbellis" created="Fri, 14 Oct 2011 02:22:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d rather raise an error server-side, than silently not do what was requested&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13127870" author="brandon.williams" created="Fri, 14 Oct 2011 21:26:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 with minor typo fixes: s/then/than/ and s/greather/greater/&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
